The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Fire on Danapur train
                                                                                                               Fire on Danapur train
                            
	Patna, July 7 (PTI): Hundreds of passengers of 553 Islampur-Danapur Passenger had a narrow escape after the train caught fire at Bankaghat railway station under East Central Railway (ECR) late last night.        
	ECR sources today said that the blaze was first noticed in the motor van and it soon spread to the adjoining coach. However, an alert railway staff detached the van from other coaches thereby averting a disaster.        
	As passengers noticed flames billowing out, they jumped out of the compartments in panic and ran for safety. There was no report of any casualty.        
	As a result of the fire, the overhead high tension wires on both up and down lines were damaged, sources said. Train services on the route was restored this morning.        
	Meanwhile, the cause behind the fire is being investigated.                                                                                                                                                                           
